stylometry: Bayes' Theorem allows you to predict what will happen with A given that B also happens.  One set of information based upon the results of another can give you a probability that allows businesses to see what will happen in their business.  It is important in order to see what the likelihood of a certain incident will be based off of another and how it responded to it.  We find posterior probabilities based off of other responses to information.  We need them to show possible trends and probabilties so that we can prepare for them.  An example would be a business that has a large customer base.  If there is a news resport that discredits their product or service, they need to be able to see what will happen to their revenue because of this report.
